Uktar 17: My loss of control alarms me. When the king's envoy came to do some
	research in our library, I nearly bit the man in two. Then I found
	myself yelling at all the young ladies of the congregation about the
	evils of men. Not preaching, yelling. Was I just envious of their
	freedom to love, to be with a man? I just ran back to my room and
	collapsed. They told me later that the envoy kept the key to the
	library. I hardly care. I am too concerned about myself and my
	church. Am I slipping into madness?

